name: CXErrorCodeRequestTransactionError.Code
desc: Error codes for the CallKit Constants error domain.

items.name: case unentitled
items.desc: The app isn’t entitled to perform the actions in the requested transaction.

items.name: case unknownCallProvider
items.desc: The controller couldn’t find a call provider to perform the actions in the requested transaction.

items.name: case emptyTransaction
items.desc: The requested transaction contains no actions.

items.name: case unknownCallUUID
items.desc: The requested transaction contains call actions that reference an unknown UUID.

items.name: case callUUIDAlreadyExists
items.desc: The requested transaction contains call actions that reference a UUID that already exists.

items.name: case invalidAction
items.desc: The requested transaction contains an invalid action.

items.name: case maximumCallGroupsReached
items.desc: The requested transaction contains actions that, if performed, would exceed the maximum number of call groups for the provider.
